702943f-a.title: Brooklyn: 100th Street (East) - Avenue K
702943f-a.text:
1117 East 100th Street, east side, between Ave. E (left) and Ave. L (right), showing a home and a group of barns as seen across clearing from Ave. K and Rockaway Parkway. Note the extensive fill, raising all of
south Brooklyn from 10 to 12 feet.
July 6, 1933.
P. L. 5perr.
